column14: Silver, gilded, rectangular headplate with spiral ornament inside border and crescent relief outside; band-shaped bow with central rib and dotted ornament on each side; two animal heads with open mouths at bow base framing a rhombic footplate with inner rhombus, undivided; frontal animal head at foot terminal.
column19: Relief fibula, silver and gold, Early Germanic Iron Age.

column14: Silver, gilded, headplate slightly rounded, almost cross-shaped, with three lateral frontal animal heads; geometric and light spiral ornament, two stylized animal heads formed; bow band-shaped with four rows of line ornament; footplate partly rectangular with symmetrical ornament, central spiral motif, two beaked animal heads above and below axis; frontal animal head at foot terminal.
column19: Relief fibula, silver and gold, Early Germanic Iron Age.
